    <persName type="additional" subtype="title">1st baronet</persName>
    
    <note type="dates"><date>1745–1828</date></note>
    
    <note type="biography">
        <p>Translator. Called to the bar, 1771. Recorder of Wigan, 1815–28; constable of Lancaster Castle; British consul, Nantes, 1825–8. Married Ann, daughter of Charles White, in 1780. Published several translations of works in French, Latin, and Italian. Created baronet, 1774.</p></note>
